@{
    ViewBag.CurrentPage = "Home";
}
<div>
    <h2>Welcome to ASP.NET Boilerplate</h2>
    <p class="lead">A starting point for web applications with best practices and most popular tools!</p>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h3>Architecture</h3>
            <p>
                ASP.NET Boilerplate implements <strong>NLayer architecture</strong> (Domain, Application, Infrastructure and Presentation Layers)
                and <strong>Domain Driven Design</strong> (Entities, Repositories, Domain/Application Services, DTO's...).
                Also implements and provides a good infrastructure to implement <strong>best practices</strong> such as <strong>Dependency Injection</strong>.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h3>Frameworks</h3>
            <p>
                ASP.NET Boilerplate is built on latest ASP.NET MVC &amp; Web API technologies.
                Uses Castle Windsor as Dependency Injection Container, NHibernate as O/RM framework, Log4Net for logging, FluentMigrator for database migrations and so on.
                Also, in client side, uses DurandalJs, KnockoutJs, jQuery, RequireJs, Less for CSS.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h3>Open source</h3>
            <p>
                ASP.NET Boilerplate is an <strong>Open Source</strong> project that is being developed under <a href="https://github.com/aspnetboilerplate" target="_blank">github</a>.
                Libraries are published on <strong>nuget</strong> for Visual Studio.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h3>Tutorials</h3>
            <p>
                Click here to read the <a href="http://www.codeproject.com/Articles/768664/Introduction-to-ASP-NET-Boilerplate" target="_blank">Introduction to ASP.NET Boilerplate</a>.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h3>Templates</h3>
            <p>
                ASP.NET Boilerplate provides templates for <strong>Single-Page Applications</strong> and Classic Multi-Page Applications.
                These templates are ready to start to develop new applications. There are also sample projects made with ASP.NET Boilerplate.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h3>Sample projects</h3>
            <p>
                See <a href="http://www.taskever.com">Taskever</a> for a comprehensive application built on ASP.NET Boilerplate. Also see <a href="https://github.com/aspnetboilerplate/aspnetboilerplate-samples">samples on github</a> for simpler sample applications.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>